ient means for calculating how\nphysical vortices mutually interact without requiring a complete construction\nof their internal structure. In passing we show why a common procedure for\ndoing so using a $\\delta$-function can lead to incorrect results. Our\nprocedures generalize straightforwardly to general co-dimension objects.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Aug 2015 18:17:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Sep 2015 04:23:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-30"}
